title: Frieze, 1890–1900
description: Border; upper half consists of series of interwined gilt circles forming a geometric pattern. In center of each is a coral colored disc in light blue field. Lower portion consists of stylized stiff sprays, three stems each ofgilt leaves under a series of three petalled formal gray-olive leaf motifs all on a bisque field. Deep coral, gold and gilt lines top, botton and in center of border. "No. 1639, Robert Graves Co." printed in selvedge.

tombstone.epitaph:
Frieze, 1890–1900.
1890–1900. Machine-printed. Gift of Robina Clark. 1939-33-47.
